The four issues the CFPB is considering regarding section 1033 of the Dodd-Frank Act are [1]:
1. The proper understanding of who can serve as a "representative" making a request on behalf of the consumer;
2. The optimal approach to the assessment of fees to defray the costs incurred by a "covered person" in responding to a customer-driven request;
3. The threat and cost-benefit pictures for data security associated with section 1033 compliance; 
4. The threat picture for data privacy associated with section 1033 compliance.
